-- mig 347 — Phase D-1: ingest 707 fetched procedure bodies into procedures.body_md_source_text.
--
-- body_md_source_text is INTERNAL — never rendered publicly. It exists so a
-- later restating pass (LLM-aided or manual) can produce the public body_md.
-- Update matches on (procedure_type, title) so the same procedure on multiple
-- gens gets the same source text (titles came from the same upstream catalog).

SET NAMES utf8mb4;

UPDATE procedures SET body_md_source_text = 'Important notes

 ''Inspection service'' is shown on the Service Interval Display (SID)

 The distance-based service and the service indicated by the service indicator can occur at the same time

 The vehicle data label shows a code that corresponds with the type of service:

 ID location

 X

 Equipment code overview

 X

 • Time/distance dependent service (QI1, QI2, QI3, QI4, QI5, QI7)

 • Longlife service (QI6, QI8)

 • Diesel not compliant with EN 590: (QI1, QI2, QI3)

 • Petrol not compliant with EN 228: (QI1, QI2, QI3)

 Service code location:

 • Owner''s manual/service record and warranty book

 • Sticker in the spare tyre wheel well/luggage compartment

 Notes:

 • The service code may not be shown on the vehicle data label

 • The service menu shows the vehicle service type

 • To access the service menu, use the vehicle information system

 • Alternatively, use a diagnostic tool

 Oil service and Time interval:

 • Every 5,000 km/12 months (QI1)

 • Every 7,500 km/12 months (QI2)

 • Every 10,000 km/12 months (QI3)

 • Every 15,000 km/12 months (QI4)

 • Every 20,000 km/12 months (QI5)

 • Flexible interval (QI6)

 • Every 10,000 miles/12 months (QI7)

 • Flexible interval (QI8)

 If a different oil than the specified longlife oil is used, the longlife service intervals are no longer valid.

 The service interval must be reprogrammed to ''non flexible''.

 A diagnostic tool must be used for this operation

 To change the service interval back to longlife, reprogram it to ''flexible'' service

 If the service interval is reset with the trip recorder buttons, the service interval is set to ''time/distance dependent''

 A diagnostic tool must be used for this operation

 Longlife service

 There are two types of service intervals

 The vehicle data label shows a code that corresponds with the type of service:

 ID location

 X

 Equipment code overview

 X

 • Time/distance dependent service (QI1, QI2, QI3, QI4, QI5, QI7)

 • Longlife service (QI6, QI8)

 Longlife service intervals have a maximum of

 • 30,000 km (20,000 miles)/24 months (QI6)

 Otherwise the service indicator on the dashboard will calculate the service interval

 Operating conditions

 In severe conditions the service intervals will be shorter

 Severe conditions apply when the vehicle is operated under one or more of the following conditions:

 • Frequent short trips of less than 16 km/10 miles

 • Prolonged idling

 • Urban driving with long idling stops

 • When using fuel with a high sulphur content

 • Driving in dusty, sandy or wet conditions

 • Frequent driving (> 50% of the time) at sustained high speeds in high temperatures (> 32 °C)

 • Frequent driving (> 50% of the time) in heavy traffic and high temperatures (> 32 °C)

 • Frequent driving at temperatures below -15 °C

 • Extreme temperatures

 • (Hybrid vehicles) Driving mainly using the electric motor; infrequent combustion engine usage' WHERE procedure_type = 'schedule_note' AND title = 'Note: Note: Read this before selecting a maintenance schedule' AND body_md_source_text IS NULL;
