 Special tools are required to determine the gearbox fluid temperature

 Draining/refilling

 Turn the engine off

 Ensure the vehicle is horizontal

 Move the gear lever to position ''P''

 Apply the parking brake

 Remove the engine lower cover

 Place a draining tray under the gearbox

 Connect the diagnostic tool

 Follow the on-screen instructions

 Remove the drain plug

 ZEnlarge

 Drain and clean the ATF sump

 Refit the drain plug

 Renew the seal

 Remove the level plug

 ZEnlarge

 Refill the gearbox hydraulic control unit

 Using a hand pump 

 (

 VAS 6617

 )

 Connect the diagnostic tool

 Follow the on-screen instructions

 Refit the level plug

 Level check

 Test conditions:

 Note: Ensure that the gearbox is not in limp home mode

 Move the gear lever to position ''P''

 Apply the parking brake

 Air conditioning OFF

 Turn the heating system off

 Connect the diagnostic tool

 Start the engine

 Check the transmission fluid temperature < 35 °C

 Check the fluid level

 Follow the on-screen instructions

 Remove the engine lower cover

 When the oil temperature reaches 35 °C

 Place a draining tray under the gearbox

 Remove the level plug

 ZEnlarge

 If ATF flows out, the level is correct

 Allow excess fluid to drain off

 Refit the level plug

 Renew the seal

 If no fluid flows out, proceed as follows:

 Check the transmission fluid temperature 45 °C

 Turn the engine off

 Allow the gearbox to cool down 35 °C

 Using a hand pump 

 (

 VAS 6617

 )

 Add 0.5 litres of ATF

 Check the fluid level

 Repeat the procedure

