UPDATE procedures SET body_md_source_text = 'Important notes

 ''Inspection service'' is shown on the Service Interval Display (SID)

 The distance-based service and the service indicated by the service indicator can occur at the same time

 The vehicle data label shows a code that corresponds with the type of service:

 ID location

 X

 • Time/distance dependent service (QI1, QI2, QI3, QI4, QI7)

 • Longlife service (QI6)

 • Diesel not compliant with EN 590: (QI1, QI2, QI3, QI4)

 • Petrol not compliant with EN 228: (QI1, QI2, QI3, QI4)

 Service code location:

 • Owner''s manual/service record and warranty book

 • Sticker in the spare tyre wheel well/luggage compartment

 Notes:

 • The service code may not be shown on the vehicle data label

 • The service menu shows the vehicle service type

 • To access the service menu, use the vehicle information system

 • Alternatively, use a diagnostic tool

 Oil service and Time interval:

 • Every 5,000 km/12 months (QI1)

 • Every 7,500 km/12 months (QI2)

 • Every 10,000 km/12 months (QI3)

 • Every 15,000 km/12 months (QI4)

 • Every 10,000 miles/12 months (QI7)

 If a different oil than the specified longlife oil is used, the longlife service intervals are no longer valid.

 The service interval must be reprogrammed to ''non flexible''.

 A diagnostic tool must be used for this operation

 To change the service interval back to longlife, reprogram it to ''flexible'' service

 If the service interval is reset with the trip recorder buttons, the service interval is set to ''time/distance dependent''

 A diagnostic tool must be used for this operation

