 Note: Carry out this procedure with the aid of a second person

 System bleeding procedure

 Bleed the brake system in the following sequence:

 Driver''s side:

 Front.

 Passenger side:

 Front.

 Driver''s side:

 Rear.

 Passenger side:

 Rear.

 Check that the fluid level is at the MAX mark

 Remove the brake fluid reservoir cap

 Remove the wheel

 Turn the ignition ON

 Connect a transparent pipe to the bleed hole

 Insert the other end of the bleed pipe into a glass container with a small quantity of brake fluid

 Press the brake pedal several times

 Press and hold the brake pedal

 Open the bleed screw

 The brake pedal will travel slowly to the floor

 Tighten the bleed screw

 Repeat the brake bleeding procedure until the new fluid in the pipe is free of air bubbles

 Check the brake fluid level

 Check for leaks

 Top up the brake fluid level to the MAX mark

 Repeat the procedure for the other brakes

 Turn the ignition OFF

 Wait for at least 3 minutes

 Do not open or close the doors

 Press the brake pedal several times

 Press and hold the brake pedal

 Open the bleed screw

 The brake pedal will travel slowly to the floor

 Tighten the bleed screw

 Repeat the brake bleeding procedure until the new fluid in the pipe is free of air bubbles

 Check the brake fluid level

 Check for leaks

 Top up the brake fluid level to the MAX mark

 Repeat the procedure for the other brakes

 Torque settings

