UPDATE procedures SET body_md_source_text = 'Important notes

 The display will show the workshop code and remaining distance/days

 ''A'' indicates a minor service, ''H'' a major service

 The letters indicate the time needed for service only A -> 1h, B -> 2h, H -> 8h

 Inspection service B

 The numbers indicate the sequence of the B services

 Examples: B1 service = first B service; B2 service = second B service, etc.

 How to display the required service positions

 ZEnlarge

 Close the bonnet

 Close all the doors

 Close the boot/tailgate

 Turn the ignition key to position ''1''

 Press button (2) repeatedly until the miles/kilometre reading appears on the display

 Press button (1) briefly 3 times

 The voltage reading appears on the multifunction display

 Press button (3) repeatedly to scroll through the list

 Until the ''Service Menu'' appears on the display

 Press button (4) repeatedly to scroll through the list

 Until ''Items'' is highlighted

 Press button (5)

 The display will now list the services to be carried out

 Make a note of the service items

 Note: Write down the numbers

 ZEnlarge

 Press button (2) repeatedly until the miles/kilometre reading appears on the display

 Turn the ignition off' WHERE procedure_type = 'schedule_note' AND title = 'Note: Note: Read this before selecting a maintenance schedule' AND body_md_source_text IS NULL;
UPDATE procedures SET body_md_source_text = 'Service indicator reset

 ZEnlarge

 Close the bonnet

 Close the boot/tailgate

 Close all the doors

 Note: The picture shows the car menu with the language set to English

 Turn the ignition key to position ''1''

 Select the miles/kilometre reading on the display

 Press button (2) repeatedly until the miles/kilometre reading appears on the display

 Press button (1) briefly 3 times

 The voltage reading appears on the multifunction display

 Press the lower scroll button (3)

 ''SERVICE MENU'' appears on the display

 Use the volume ''+'' and ''-'' buttons (4) to select ''CONFIRMATION'' from the menu

 Confirm the selection by pressing the lower button (2)

 The ''FULL SERVICE'' menu is highlighted

 Confirm the selection by pressing the lower button (2)

 ''SERVICE CONFIRMED'' appears on the display

 Press the upper button (2) repeatedly until ''SERVICE MENU'' appears on the display

 Press the volume ''+'' and ''-'' buttons (4) to scroll through the list

 until menu item ''ADDITIONAL WORK'' is highlighted

 Confirm the selection by pressing the lower button (2)

 Press the volume ''+'' and ''-'' buttons (4) to scroll through the list

 until menu item ''Service 3'' is highlighted

 Confirm the selection by pressing the lower button (2)

 Use the volume ''+'' and ''-'' buttons (4) to select the oil specification being used

 Confirm the selection by pressing the lower button (2)

 ''POSITION CONFIRMED'' appears on the display

 Press the upper button (2) repeatedly until the miles/kilometre reading appears on the display

 Turn the ignition key to position ''0''

 The system is reset' WHERE procedure_type = 'service_reset' AND title = 'Service indicator reset' AND body_md_source_text IS NULL;
