 Important notes

 The distance-based service and the service indicated by the service indicator can occur at the same time

 If a different oil than the specified longlife oil is used, the longlife service intervals are no longer valid.

 The service interval must be reprogrammed to ''non flexible''.

 A diagnostic tool must be used for this operation

 To change the service interval back to longlife, reprogram it to ''flexible'' service

 If the service interval is reset with the trip recorder buttons, the service interval is set to ''time/distance dependent''

 A diagnostic tool must be used for this operation

 Longlife service

 There are two types of service intervals

 The vehicle data label shows a code that corresponds with the type of service:

 ID location

 X

 Equipment code overview

 X

 • Longlife service (QG1)

 • Time/distance dependent service (QG0, QG2)

 Note: The ''QG0'' equipment level is not fitted with components that allow a flexible service, but the ''QG2'' equipment level can be recoded to flexible service

 Longlife service intervals have a maximum of

 • 30,000 km (20,000 miles)/24 months for petrol engines

 • 50,000 km (30,000 miles)/24 months for diesel engines

 • 30,000 km (20,000 miles)/24 months for engines with diesel particulate filter

 Otherwise the service indicator on the dashboard will calculate the service interval

 Non-compliant diesel

 Diesel not compliant with EN 590:

 • When using fuel with a high sulphur content :

 • When using fuel with a biodiesel content

