 Maximum number of programmable remote controls: 4

 Use the car key to operate the central locking

 Close all the doors

 Keys can only be programmed with a diagnostic tool DIS

 Programming keys

 Turn the ignition key to position ''1''

 Within 5 seconds

 Turn the ignition off

 At the radio transmitter:

 Press and hold the button 2

 Press button (1) briefly 3 times

 Within 10 seconds

 Release the button 2

 The door locks will operate

 This indicates that the remote control has been successfully programmed

 After 30 seconds the programming mode starts automatically

 Repeat the procedure for all remaining remote controls

 The programming mode will exit if:

 The door locks will not operate

 No new key/remote control is programmed within the time limit

 Button cell renewal

