 The toe and the camber angles cannot be adjusted separately

 Use the following graph to obtain the specific values:

 The ''T'' axis shows the toe (in minutes)

 The ''C'' axis shows the camber (in minutes)

 The ''W'' line shows the toe/camber values obtained by using the eccentric bolt on the wishbone

 The ''S'' line shows the toe/camber values obtained by using the eccentric bolt on the swinging arm

 ZEnlarge

 Phase 1:

 Using the eccentric bolt on the wishbone, adjust the toe/camber to one of the values set by the ''S'' line on the graph

 The toe/camber values will move parallel with the ''W'' line on the graph

 Phase 2:

 Using the eccentric bolt on the swinging arm, adjust the toe/camber to the set value shown at the intersection of the ''S'' and ''W'' lines on the graph

 The toe/camber values will move along the ''S'' line on the graph

 Example:

 Measurement value (1: T=-10''; C=-90'')

 Phase 1:

 Using the eccentric bolt on the wishbone, adjust the toe/camber to one of the values set by the ''S'' line on the graph (2: T=-2''; C=-98'')

 The toe/camber values will move parallel with the ''W'' line on the graph

 Phase 2:

 Using the eccentric bolt on the swinging arm, adjust the toe/camber to the set value shown at the intersection of the ''S'' and ''W'' lines on the graph (3: T=7''; C=- 90'')

 The toe/camber values will move along the ''S'' line on the graph

