UPDATE procedures SET body_md_source_text = 'General

 The vehicle is equipped with ''Condition Based Servicing''

 Note: Do not carry out the reset procedure until the maintenance operations are complete

 The on-board computer clock must be correct

 If the battery is disconnected, the on-board computer clock stops at the time of disconnection

 Each service item reset is counted internally

 The counter is used to determine if extra service is needed

 Note: The reset procedure will only function if the service item is at 80% or less of its lifetime

 Note: The brakes service item can only be reset if the brake wear sensor is working correctly

 Once the service has been carried out, reset each appropriate icon

 Display icons which are used: 

 X

 Service indicator reset

 Proceed as follows:

 Close all the doors

 Insert the key card into the ignition slot

 Do not press any of the pedals

 Press the start/stop button twice to turn the ignition on

 Press the start/stop button to turn the ignition off

 Press the start/stop button to turn the ignition on

 Note: Before carrying out the reset procedure, it may be necessary to display the clock

 ZEnlarge

 Press and hold the trip recorder button (1)

 Wait for 10 seconds

 The first service item will be shown

 Release the trip recorder button (1)

 The service items will be shown in order of priority

 Press button (2) repeatedly to scroll through the list

 Select the service items by moving the toggle switch up or down

 Press button (3)

 Press the button until ''RESET'' appears on the display

 Press and hold the button to confirm the reset

 Note: During the reset, a clock symbol is shown

 After a successful reset, a marker will appear (shown on the display) behind the text ''RESET''

 Release button (3)

 Turn the ignition off

 If more services need to be reset, repeat this procedure

 Periodical inspection (if applicable)

 To reset the system:

 Start the engine

 Wait for 10 seconds

 Stop the engine

 Start the engine

 Note: Before carrying out the reset procedure, it may be necessary to display the clock

 Press and hold the trip recorder button (1)

 Wait for 10 seconds

 The first service item will be shown

 Release the trip recorder button (1)

 The service items will be shown in order of priority

 Select the service items by moving the toggle switch up or down (I)

 ZEnlarge

 Press button (3)

 To select the date:

 Select the service items by moving the toggle switch up or down

 Confirm the selection by pressing button (3)

