 System bleeding procedure

 Connect the diagnostic tool

 Select ''Service functions''

 Select ''Chassis and suspension''

 Select ''Integrated brake system''

 Select ''Brake fluid renewal''

 Follow the instructions on the screen of the diagnostic tool

 Remove the brake fluid reservoir cap

 Note: Clean off the area first

 Connect the brake bleeding equipment to the brake fluid reservoir.

 Use approved brake bleeding equipment.

 Slowly increase the pressure

 Pressure: (2.0 bar)

 Using the jacking points, raise the vehicle

 Bleed the brake system in the following sequence:

 • Rear right brake (1)

 • Rear left brake (2)

 • Front right brake (3)

 • Front left brake (4)

 Attach a hose to the bleeder plug

 Place the other end into a clean container

 Open the bleed screw

 Bleed the brake system

 Leave the bleed screw open until new brake fluid flows out without bubbles

 Tighten the bleed screw

 Repeat the procedure for the other brakes

 Lower the vehicle

 Check the brake fluid level; top up if necessary

 Refit the brake fluid reservoir cap

 Check the entire braking system for leaks

 Torque settings

