UPDATE procedures SET body_md_source_text = 'General

 The vehicle is equipped with ''Condition Based Servicing''

 Note: Do not carry out the reset procedure until the maintenance operations are complete

 The on-board computer clock must be correct

 If the battery is disconnected, the on-board computer clock stops at the time of disconnection

 Each service item reset is counted internally

 The counter is used to determine if extra service is needed

 Note: The reset procedure will only function if the service item is at 90% or less of its lifetime

 Note: The brakes service item can only be reset if the brake wear sensor is working correctly

 Once the service has been carried out, reset each appropriate icon

 Display icons which are used: 

 X

 Service indicator reset

 Close all the doors

 Turn the electric vehicle (EV) power switch ON

 Press the start/stop button quickly 3 times

 Press and hold button (1).

 Wait for 10 seconds.

 The first service item will be shown

 Press button (1) repeatedly to scroll through the list

 ZEnlarge

 Select the appropriate operation from the menu

 ''Reset possible'' appears on the display

 ''Perform reset?'' appears on the display

 Press and hold button (1) for 3 seconds

 ''Reset successful'' appears on the display

 The service item has been reset

 Repeat the procedure if required' WHERE procedure_type = 'service_reset' AND title = 'Service indicator reset' AND body_md_source_text IS NULL;
